rmance in scenarios involving large articulations, partial occlusions, or cross-category motion transfer (e.g., human-to-animal gait mimicry). Our framework supports real-time inference through cached kernel generation and low-resolution warping upscaling, and it naturally integrates with existing NeRF pipelines. Ultimately, this work establishes a new direction in 3D-aware motion control: not by modifying features, but by intelligently relocating them according to learned motion semantics—bridging the gap between correspondence learning and neural scene representation.",
